TERMS

1. OPEN SOURCE REQUIREMENT
All modifications, derivatives, and linked works must be released under this 
license. Source code must be available to all users interacting with the software 
over a network (AGPLv3 Section 13).

2. INDIGENOUS SOVEREIGNTY CLAUSE
Software deployed on Akimel O'odham or Piipaash territories must respect 
community veto power over land-use, water-allocation, and data-sovereignty 
functions. Removal of sovereignty checks (e.g., 'is_indigenous_sovereign' flags) 
is a material breach of this license.

3. NEURORIGHTS PROTECTION
Biometric, biosignal, and neural data collected by this software must be:
  a) Encrypted locally before transmission (Zero-Knowledge).
  b) Deletable upon user request (Right to Purge).
  c) Used only for explicit, consented purposes (No Behavioral Prediction).

4. ECOLOGICAL STABILITY
Software controlling environmental systems (water, energy, waste) must enforce 
Lyapunov stability constraints ($V_t$ non-increasing). Modifications that 
allow environmental degradation (e.g., overriding toxicity corridors) are 
prohibited.

5. BLACKLIST COMPLIANCE
Use of blacklisted algorithms (SHA-256, BLAKE, KECCAK, Python for core logic) 
voids this license. Only supported languages (Rust, ALN, Lua, JS, Kotlin, C++) 
and post-quantum safe cryptography are permitted.

6. OFFLINE CAPABILITY
Deployments must maintain ≥72 hours of autonomous operation without network 
connectivity. Cloud-only dependencies are prohibited for critical infrastructure.

7. LIABILITY
Contributors are liable for intentional violations of sovereignty, neurorights, 
or ecological stability constraints. Accidental errors must be patched within 
72 hours of disclosure.

8. TERMINATION
License terminates automatically upon violation of Terms 2, 3, or 4. Reinstatement 
requires community consent (Indigenous) or user consent (Neurorights).

DISCLAIMER
SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. AUTHORS ARE NOT 
LIABLE FOR DAMAGES EXCEPT IN CASES OF GROSS NEGLIGENCE OR INTENTIONAL HARM.

END OF TERMS
